Pour cooled grease into a small glass cup or bowl with a wick in it.. Tie a cotton string to the middle of a stick or toothpick (depending upon the width of the cup or bowl). You want most of the string to hang into the bacon grease with a small amount sticking up on top. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/1/13/Reuse-Bacon-Grease-Step-10Bullet1.jpg/v4-459px-Reuse-Bacon-Grease-Step-10Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/1/13/Reuse-Bacon-Grease-Step-10Bullet1.jpg/v4-759px-Reuse-Bacon-Grease-Step-10Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Lay the toothpick or stick across the top of the jar or cup. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/a/aa/Reuse-Bacon-Grease-Step-10Bullet2.jpg/v4-459px-Reuse-Bacon-Grease-Step-10Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/a/aa/Reuse-Bacon-Grease-Step-10Bullet2.jpg/v4-759px-Reuse-Bacon-Grease-Step-10Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Light the top of the string and allow it to burn. After 15 to 30 minutes the bacon grease becomes a solid. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/1/1e/Reuse-Bacon-Grease-Step-10Bullet3.jpg/v4-459px-Reuse-Bacon-Grease-Step-10Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/1/1e/Reuse-Bacon-Grease-Step-10Bullet3.jpg/v4-759px-Reuse-Bacon-Grease-Step-10Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
